.TH "snd_pcm_hw_param_first" 9 "snd_pcm_hw_param_first" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_hw_param_first \- refine config space and return minimum value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_hw_param_first
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *pcm "  ","
.BI "struct snd_pcm_hw_params *params "  ","
.BI "snd_pcm_hw_param_t var "  ","
.BI "int *dir "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pcm" 12
PCM instance
.IP "params" 12
the hw_params instance
.IP "var" 12
parameter to retrieve
.IP "dir" 12
pointer to the direction (-1,0,1) or NULL
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Inside configuration space defined by \fIparams\fP remove from \fIvar\fP all
values > minimum. Reduce configuration space accordingly.
.SH "RETURN"
The minimum, or a negative error code on failure.
